{
  "stem": "3949.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, it just-- you know, we looked like-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's just unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyway, I was standing right to my sister, and I was hollering for her, Frieda, Frieda.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was hollering for me, because we just didn't recognize each other.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And after that, I-- I just got a hold of her.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I shouldn't lose her, because I wouldn't-- Did they just cut your hair short when you said they cut your hair?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not short-- bald.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Bald.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were just bald.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they promised that we gonna be reunited with our family on Sunday.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But that was just the very, very first lie what they told us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That Sunday never came.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- I-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, after that--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--she was-- she was hiding.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I always-- I had to-- right away, we had to stand up five in a row, like soldiers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she was the very first one always in the-- in the line.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had to be behind her all the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So this way-- and my aunt was-- actually, five of us made a row, because my brother's fiancee, and her aunt, and my aunt.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we made five in a row.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's the was we were always standing there when we were counted for appells, like when Mengele came and looking us over every single day to see-- he was-- who was, you know, sickly and-- and who could go to work.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, first of all, when we were selected to be sent to the right side, that-- that was a good sign, because, you know, we know we were gonna go to work.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The one who, like my mother, and her sister, and the children, were put to the left.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
